fields.name: Zalora
fields.description: ZALORA is an e-commerce platform and website that provides top international & local brands across fashion and footwear products across 6 markets in South East Asia
fields.customer_demographics: Fashion forward and fashion conscious male & female customer aged 20-40. Insights will vary across 6 markets according to physical retail channels, brands already available in the market & general income levels.

fields.name: Newegg Inc
fields.description: Newegg is the #1 online Marketplace for everything tech in the US. Sell your products to over 30 million interested customers.
fields.customer_demographics: 63% Male,37% Female customers, 51% earn $60K+, 22% earn $100K+. Over 2.3M social fans across 9 platforms, 3M+ customer product reviews.

fields.name: Otto
fields.description: Otto.de is an award winning e-marketplace that has grown from a 60 year catalogue business to become a household name in Germany.
fields.customer_demographics: 6 Million active customers, women age 25-55, 62% are married females, above average income
fields.marketing_merchandising: 6 in-house blogs (Two For Fashion, Soulfully, RE:blog, Rombeez) , special ad types (Banners), TV ads, Print advertising, Posters, Catalogue, Social Media, Online branding

fields.name: XIU
fields.description: China e-retailer with a 12 million customer base. It is rated as No.1 China fashion online retailer by third party research institutions
fields.customer_demographics: Middle class, upper middleclass and upper class women. Ages are 18 plus
fields.marketing_merchandising: This is a key element for success in China. Xiu.com are willing to handle your marketing budget if you will commit to them exclusively and not be on other platforms the brand is advised to add back 30% of turnover into their marketing. xiu.com will offer basic promotion on the site.

fields.name: Tmall Global
fields.description: Launched in February 2014, Tmall Global (TMG) is a cross border ecommerce marketplace in China
fields.marketing_merchandising: Marketing and brand promotion is a pre-requisite for success in China. This is considered to be 30% of revenue at least for the fist 12-18 months. This can be carried out by the TP or a specialist marketoing agency. Other on platform promotions involved special discounts are also encouraged.

fields.name: VIP Shop
fields.description: Launched in Sep 2014, VIP Global is an independent channel on VIP.com selling only foreign brands
fields.customer_demographics: 75% of registered users are females aged 18 - 45 yrs.
fields.marketing_merchandising: Launched in Sep 2014, VIP Global is an independent channel on VIP.com selling only foreign brands. The overall VIP.com (NYSE: VIPS) is ranked as the 3rd in terms of the sales scale which reached 6.2 billion USD by end of 2015. Pricing is set by agreement between VIP and partner brands. VIP sells both in season and off season products. Brands have also found success in leveraging the great VIP customer base to launch new season product lines at full price. VIP has set up 10 offices internationally working closely with brands directly to select products and providing international logistics supports to brands and cross-boarder delivery service to customers.19.7 million active users by Q1 2016, 100 million registered users.

fields.name: 1688.com
fields.description: Alibaba's 1688 B2B ecommerce platform is the largest in country wholesale trading site for FMCG products in China.
fields.customer_demographics: Businesses purchasing imported products from 1688 will be targetting the rising middle class in China; British brands are attractive as they satisfy the customer requirements for quality, heritage, health and innovation.
fields.marketing_merchandising: 1688 is an ideal marketing and sales platform and The British Pavilion identifies and negotiates with Chinese distributors & retailers; pricing structures will be agreed allowing for volume & promotional discounts.

fields.name: Alibaba Direct
fields.marketing_merchandising: Established recognition is pre-requisite condition. Direct Buy team will work with the brand to leverage its existing marketing resources in home country, and produce localised marketing information which to be promoted in Alibaba's own marketing channels.

fields.name: Shangpin
fields.description: As the leading Luxury and fashion online platform in China, Shangpin was established in 2010 covering over 1400 brands.
fields.customer_demographics: 60% Women 40% Men, fashion conscious 16 years and up. Average basket size is $200 and repeat purchase rates of 80%
fields.marketing_merchandising: Shangpin have 10 Photographic teams for imagery, they work with a group of celebrities, and partner with reality show Muse Dress as well as running general marketing and promotions

fields.name: JD Worldwide
fields.description: JD Worldwide is one of the business sectors under JD.com, which operates products from overseas in the form of cross boarder e-commerce only.
fields.customer_demographics: Male and female , aged 16-55 years old; target consumer: middle-class
fields.marketing_merchandising: Setting up Wechat Shops; Website frontpage advertisement; Top locations in product searching etc. *all with extra charge paid by sellers

fields.name: Allegro
fields.description: Over 18 million Poles visit Allegro.pl monthly, contributing to the sale of over 750,000 items on the platform every day.
fields.customer_demographics: 47% Male, 53% Female; Age: 26% - 15-24 years old, 34% - 25 -24 years old, 34% - 35-49 years old, City population 39% - Cities with up to 200k residents
fields.marketing_merchandising: Allegro ads system, Promotional options: Featuring, Highlighting, Bolding, Promotion on department Page, Daily Deals, Brand Zone, Ad Placements: showcase on main page, landing pages, etc.

fields.name: Spartoo
fields.description: Spartoo.co.uk is an e-commerce website specialising in shoes and clothing created in 2009 as part of the company Spartoo.com, created in 2006 and based in Grenoble, France
fields.marketing_merchandising: No merchandising, 12 million spent on online marketing per year

fields.name: FlipKart
fields.description: Flipkart is India's largest e-commerce marketplace, with over 65% market share in major categories.
fields.marketing_merchandising: As per the plan mutually decided between brand and Flipkart

fields.name: TradeMe
fields.description: Trade Me is New Zealand's most popular website and largest digital platform, focused on delivering awesome online experiences to Kiwis across all aspects of their lives.
fields.customer_demographics: 85% of the population of New Zealand hold an account with TradeMe so the platform reaches a very broad demographic spread.
fields.marketing_merchandising: 75% of all domestic web traffic in New Zealand goes to TradeMe. TradeMe offers the following marketing for the right brand. 1. Display advertising across site, 2. Solus email marketing, 3. Newsletter inclusion (1.6 million subscribers), 4. Social media push (100k FB, 17K Twitter). We may also consider external marketing for the right brand.
